[% HORIZONTAL RULE CYAN %][% BOLD %][% B_CYAN %][% BLACK %] MENUS[% RESET %]

BBS::Universal uses a specialized menu file format.  Each file is divided into two sections separated by a line with "---" by itseld.

[% BOLD %][% B_YELLOW %][% BLACK %] TEXT MODES [% RESET %][% YELLOW %]ðŸ­¬[% RESET %]

The BBS can operate in three different text modes:

 * [% BOLD %]ASCII[% RESET %] - Plain text mode
 * [% BOLD %]ATASCII[% RESET %] - Atari 8 bit text mode
 * [% BOLD %]ANSII[% RESET %] - ANSI color and graphics characters mode.  It can support 16 color, 256 color and 24 bit color codes.
 * [% BOLD %]PETSCII[% RESET %] - Commodore 8 bit color and graphics characters mode.

There is a menu file for each text mode.  The body name is the same for all modes, but the file extension is the name of the text mode.

[% BOLD %][% B_YELLOW %][% BLACK %] MENU SETUP [% RESET %][% YELLOW %]ðŸ­¬[% RESET %]

Each menu entry requires the following on a single line per entry, each variable separated by the pipe character "|"

 * [% BOLD %]Key[% RESET %]
 * [% BOLD %]Command Token[% RESET %]
 * [% BOLD %]Color[% RESET %]
 * [% BOLD %]Access Level[% RESET %] (Only for user menus)
 * [% BOLD %]Description[% RESET %]

All menu entries are sorted alphabetically by Key.

[% BOLD %][% B_YELLOW %][% BLACK %] MENU BODY [% RESET %][% YELLOW %]ðŸ­¬[% RESET %]

You can place any text and tokens (even raw codes) you want in this section.

